<span id="freeTextContainer14516853720393512864">I’ve been reading this book on and off for awhile now. I read some and put it away. Remembered it and pulled it out to read some more. Finally I just had to finish it. It had been haunting me. <br/><br/> I found it well researched. Of course, the history is somewhat bleak. But what do you expect from the Middle East? Which is too bad seeing as the region is so beautiful, and the history so deep and rich and interesting. You can’t help but wonder about the turmoil that has gone on there for so long. <br/><br/>So I l</span>
  <span id="freeText14516853720393512864" style="display:none">I’ve been reading this book on and off for awhile now. I read some and put it away. Remembered it and pulled it out to read some more. Finally I just had to finish it. It had been haunting me. <br /><br /> I found it well researched. Of course, the history is somewhat bleak. But what do you expect from the Middle East? Which is too bad seeing as the region is so beautiful, and the history so deep and rich and interesting. You can’t help but wonder about the turmoil that has gone on there for so long. <br /><br />So I liked it. If you’re not a history nerd or into this type of thing you might find it long and boring and end up using it for a doorstop instead. <br /></span>
